Parliament, Monday, 26 February 2018 – The Standing Committee on Public Accounts (Scopa) will tomorrow hold a hearing with the Department of Water and Sanitation on irregular, fruitless and wasteful expenditure, accruals and commitments. Details of the meeting: Date: Tuesday, 27 February 2018 Time: 09:00 Venue: Committee Room V454, Fourth Floor, Old Assembly Building ISSUED BY PARLIAMENTARY COMMUNICATION SERVICES ON BEHALF OF THE CHAIRPERSON OF SCOPA, MR THEMBA GODI For media enquiries, please contact the Media Officer: Name: Ms Faith Ndenze
